  "rationale": "WoodWave has no logo-wall or feature-grid, so the brief's grid-shaped copy is remapped onto editorial vocabulary. The page opens with the ONLY inverse bookend hero (hero-split-media-copy) carrying the single page accent on its display title over the staircase photo \u2014 the sole sanctioned text-on-media, stacked with overlap. The three value_props are rendered as ONE novel editorial-collage run (novelty:novel \u2014 the library lacks an open 3-module light-canvas feature run; cards-on-cream is forbidden) using open feature-item modules staggered behind a ghost word, so N props stay N modules without boxes. The gallery adapts gallery-mosaic-with-overflow into a drawable collage (bento is not a drawable archetype) with right-edge bleed, ghost word, stagger and a marginal caption \u2014 the on-brand answer to no-text-on-photos, using only the two real assets plus one brand-supplied frame. Social proof (stat + quote) maps onto a panel split since there is no logo wall; the logos flag is intentionally dropped (gap noted) and expressed as the '10,000+ teams' stat instead. The page closes on a centered conversion stack \u2014 centering reserved for the bookend/CTA per no-centered-everything \u2014 with both CTAs as typographic arrow/slash links, never buttons. Every non-hero section is primary/panel with no accent, honoring single-accent and inverse-bookend fidelity."
